# Document template custom fields

Before designing or implementing template field definitions, document field values, template editor UI, or document form merge/save:

1. Read [docs/database/templateCustomFields.md](../../docs/database/templateCustomFields.md) — approved architecture (not yet in v4 schema).
2. Read [docs/database/projectDB.md](../../docs/database/projectDB.md) for the **shipped** schema; when migrations or IPC land, update **projectDB.md in the same commit** per [docs-database.mdc](docs-database.mdc).

## Non-negotiable design rules

- **Stable `field_id`** — document values reference UUID field ids, never labels or sort order.
- **Live template + soft-delete** — field definitions use soft-delete (`deleted_at_ms` or equivalent); do not hard-delete definitions when a field is removed from the form.
- **Orphan retention** — removing a field or switching templates hides values in the main UI; **do not** auto-delete value or link rows.
- **Merge at read time** — documents store values only; merge active field definitions with stored values when loading for edit.
- **Hybrid storage** — relational `template_fields`; typed scalar rows; junction tables for M:N relationship fields (mirror `document_media` pattern).
- **Type changes** — block, assign a new `field_id`, or require explicit user review; never silently coerce stored values.
- **No template versioning in v1** — do not pin documents to `template_version_id` until a future explicit feature ships.

